iving growth through web social and mobile platforms for avon representatives and consumers driving improved service and efficiency through erp and providing data and analytics to enable growth strategiesherlihy joined avon in march  from the wrigley company where he also was cio in his  years at wrigley he drove the transformation of wrigley’s business processes enabled by a global implementation of sap in addition to leading it he also served successively as vice president of human resources and vice president of supply chainprior to wrigley he spent six years at gillette ultimately leading information technology at its duracell subsidiary earlier in his career herlihy was based in the uk where he worked in manufacturing business process reengineering and information technology in both the consumer goods and automotive sectorshe holds a bachelor of science degree in industrial engineering from dublin institute of technology  trinity college dublin ireland and he has completed the executive program at the university of michigan ross school of businesshe is a board member of the american red cross new yorkcio and vp supply chainwrigleydecember  – february   years  monthsvp supply chain and chief information officer cio for the wrigley company responsible for the strategic direction for the global supply chain and for all aspects of information technology it as cio he drove the transformation of the company’s organization and business processes enabled by a global implementation of sap in  also served as vice president  human resources for the wrigley companydirector itgillette –   yearsled it for the duracell divisionit manager  ukparker pen ltdjanuary  – july   years  monthsbusiness analystlucas diesel systems –   yearsorganizationsred crossskillsit strategystrategyleadershipcrossfunctional team leadershipsupply chain managementstrategic planningecommerceerp implementationsmanagementit managementchange managementbusiness transformationprocess improvementproject por